functionModuleRemovedTrap.name: functionModuleRemovedTrap
functionModuleRemovedTrap.description: Indicates that a function module has been removed. This includes SRM removal.

functionModuleInsertedTrap.name: functionModuleInsertedTrap
functionModuleInsertedTrap.description: Indicates that a function module has been inserted. This includes SRM insertion.

functionModuleSwitchoverTrap.name: functionModuleSwitchoverTrap
functionModuleSwitchoverTrap.description: Indicates that a function module has changed state from standby to active or vice versa

functionModuleActiveTrap.name: functionModuleActiveTrap
functionModuleActiveTrap.description: Indicates that a function module is operational

functionModuleFailedTrap.name: functionModuleFailedTrap
functionModuleFailedTrap.description: Indicates that a function module is inoperational

functionModuleMismatchTrap.name: functionModuleMismatchTrap
functionModuleMismatchTrap.description: Informational alarm generated due to a) different front card inserted b) same front card with a different feature list is inserted

functionModuleSlefTestFailedTrap.name: functionModuleSlefTestFailedTrap
functionModuleSlefTestFailedTrap.description: Indicates that a function module self test failed. Not generated when self test passes

functionModuleStandbyTrap.name: functionModuleStandbyTrap
functionModuleStandbyTrap.description: Indicates that a function module is in standby state

lineModuleRemovedTrap.name: lineModuleRemovedTrap
lineModuleRemovedTrap.description: Indicates whether or not a particular line line module has been removed

lineModuleInsertedTrap.name: lineModuleInsertedTrap
lineModuleInsertedTrap.description: Indicates whether or not a particular line line module has been inserted

lineModuleMismatchTrap.name: lineModuleMismatchTrap
lineModuleMismatchTrap.description: Indicates that the front card does not support the line module.

coreCardSwitchTrap.name: coreCardSwitchTrap
coreCardSwitchTrap.description: The standby cards have become active, due to the failure of the active cards. The log in the card, shows the reason the cards are ASC and BNM.

coreCardSwitchInProgress.name: coreCardSwitchInProgress
coreCardSwitchInProgress.description: This indicates that the switchcc process is in progress, that all the initial checks for switchcc to happen were successful.

coreCardSwitchBlocked.name: coreCardSwitchBlocked
coreCardSwitchBlocked.description: This indicates that the switchcc process cannot happen due to the checks failing. Hence a switchcc blocked trap is being sent . more like a failure trap

coreCardsConfigMismatchTrap.name: coreCardsConfigMismatchTrap
coreCardsConfigMismatchTrap.description: Mismatch between the core card configuration and the physical core cards in the system, e.g., if ASC card has configuration for a BNM-T3 card but a BNM-E3 card is plugged in.

coreCardsPeerMismatchTrap.name: coreCardsPeerMismatchTrap
coreCardsPeerMismatchTrap.description: Mismatch between two core card sets, e.g., one set has BNM-T3 but another set has BNM-E3.

coreCardsConfigClearTrap.name: coreCardsConfigClearTrap
coreCardsConfigClearTrap.description: Sent when the config is cleared.

cardResPartTypeChangeTrap.name: cardResPartTypeChangeTrap
cardResPartTypeChangeTrap.description: This trap is sent out when the resource partition type is changed. The possible changes for cardLcnPartitionType are: 1: no partition, 2: controller based, 3: port controller based

bnmTemperatureNormalTrap.name: bnmTemperatureNormalTrap
bnmTemperatureNormalTrap.description: Indicates the temperature is within the normal range

bnmTemperatureAboveNormalTrap.name: bnmTemperatureAboveNormalTrap
bnmTemperatureAboveNormalTrap.description: Indicates the temperature has exceeded the upper limit of its normal range

bnmDclevelNormalTrap.name: bnmDclevelNormalTrap
bnmDclevelNormalTrap.description: Indicates that the shelf is within its normal DC level

bnmDclevelBelowNormalTrap.name: bnmDclevelBelowNormalTrap
bnmDclevelBelowNormalTrap.description: Indicates that the shelf is DC level below the normal DC level

bnmPowersupplyNormalTrap.name: bnmPowersupplyNormalTrap
bnmPowersupplyNormalTrap.description: Indicates the shelfs power supply status is normal

bnmPowersupplyFailedTrap.name: bnmPowersupplyFailedTrap
bnmPowersupplyFailedTrap.description: Indicates the shelfs power supply status has Failed

bnmFanrpmNormalTrap.name: bnmFanrpmNormalTrap
bnmFanrpmNormalTrap.description: Indicates that a particular fan's RPM Normal

bnmFanrpmBelowNormalTrap.name: bnmFanrpmBelowNormalTrap
bnmFanrpmBelowNormalTrap.description: Indicates that a particular fan's RPM below Normal

shelfIntegratedAlarmTrap.name: shelfIntegratedAlarmTrap
shelfIntegratedAlarmTrap.description: Indicates that the shelf integrated alarm status is changed and sends the status of the shelf integrated alarm. The shelfFilteredAlarm contains the alarm status of a filtered subset of all node alarms.

userLoginTrap.name: userLoginTrap
userLoginTrap.description: Indicates that a user logged in

shelfLossLmiAlarmTrap.name: shelfLossLmiAlarmTrap
shelfLossLmiAlarmTrap.description: Indicates the Loss of LMI Alarm for AXIS BNM trunk. (ANNEX G signalling failure)

shelfLossLmiAlarmClearTrap.name: shelfLossLmiAlarmClearTrap
shelfLossLmiAlarmClearTrap.description: Indicates the Clear of Loss of LMI Alarm for AXIS BNM trunk. (ANNEX G signalling failure has cleared)

bnmNolinealarmTrapnum.name: bnmNolinealarmTrapnum
bnmNolinealarmTrapnum.description: Indicates no line alarm, obsoleted from AXIS4.0

bnmlinealarmTrapnum.name: bnmlinealarmTrapnum
bnmlinealarmTrapnum.description: Indicates line alarm exists, obsoleted from AXIS4.0 0x01 rcvRAIstate 0x02 xmtRAIstate 0x04 rcvAISstate 0x08 xmtAISstate 0x10 rcvOOFstate 0x20 rcvLOSstate

bnmLineLpbkEnableTrapnum.name: bnmLineLpbkEnableTrapnum
bnmLineLpbkEnableTrapnum.description: Indicates that line loopback has been enabled, obsoleted from AXIS4.0

bnmLineLpbkDisableTrapnum.name: bnmLineLpbkDisableTrapnum
bnmLineLpbkDisableTrapnum.description: Indicates that line loopback has been disabled, obsoleted from AXIS 4.0

dsx3LineLpbkEnableTrap.name: dsx3LineLpbkEnableTrap
dsx3LineLpbkEnableTrap.description: Indicates that line loopback has been enabled

dsx3LineLpbkDisableTrap.name: dsx3LineLpbkDisableTrap
dsx3LineLpbkDisableTrap.description: Indicates that line loopback has been disabled.

sonetLineInAlarmTrap.name: sonetLineInAlarmTrap
sonetLineInAlarmTrap.description: Indicates line alarm exists. Note that the value sent in cwSonetLineCurrentStatus in this trap contains information for all the three sonet layers (section, line, path) and also the loopback state. So it doesn't match the description provided for the cwSonetLineCurrentStatus object under `cwSonetLineCurrentTable'. The various bits in cwSonetLineCurrentStatus are: bit 1 sonetLineRcvRAI bit 2 sonetLineXmtRAI bit 3 sonetLineRcvAIS bit 4 sonetLineXmtAIS bit 5 sonetSectionRcvOOF bit 6 sonetSectionRcvLOS bit 7 localLoopBack bit 8 remoteLoopBack bit 9 remotePayloadLoopBack bit 10 sonetPathRcvLOCD bit 11 sonetPathRcvLOP bit 12 sonetPathRcvAis bit 13 sonetPathXmtAis bit 14 sonetPathRcvRdi bit 15 sonetPathXmtRdi

sonetLineNoAlarmTrap.name: sonetLineNoAlarmTrap
sonetLineNoAlarmTrap.description: Indicates line alarm has cleared Please refer to sonetLineInAlarmTrap for the format of cwSonetLineCurrentStatus

sonetLineLpbkEnableTrapnum.name: sonetLineLpbkEnableTrapnum
sonetLineLpbkEnableTrapnum.description: Indicates that line loopback has been enabled Please refer to sonetLineInAlarmTrap for the format of cwSonetLineCurrentStatus

sonetLineLpbkDisableTrapnum.name: sonetLineLpbkDisableTrapnum
sonetLineLpbkDisableTrapnum.description: Indicates that line loopback has been disabled. Please refer to sonetLineInAlarmTrap for the format of cwSonetLineCurrentStatus

dsx3StatLineAlarmTrap.name: dsx3StatLineAlarmTrap
dsx3StatLineAlarmTrap.description: Indicates the current statistical alarm State

bnmStatSonetSectionalmTrapnum.name: bnmStatSonetSectionalmTrapnum
bnmStatSonetSectionalmTrapnum.description: Indicates the current sonet section statistical alarm State

bnmStatSonetLinealmTrapnum.name: bnmStatSonetLinealmTrapnum
bnmStatSonetLinealmTrapnum.description: Indicates the current sonet Line statistical alarm State

bnmStatSonetPathalmTrapnum.name: bnmStatSonetPathalmTrapnum
bnmStatSonetPathalmTrapnum.description: Indicates the current sonet Path statistical alarm State

bnmPlcpAlmActiveTrap.name: bnmPlcpAlmActiveTrap
bnmPlcpAlmActiveTrap.description: Indicates that no PLCP alarm exists

trapBERTStart.name: trapBERTStart
trapBERTStart.description: Sent when BERT is configured and started.

trapBERTEnd.name: trapBERTEnd
trapBERTEnd.description: Sent when the ongoing BERT is stopped.

trapBERTAbort.name: trapBERTAbort
trapBERTAbort.description: This is sent out when ongoing BERT is aborted due to state changes of the cards that BERT involves namely ASC, SRM and SM. The test will be aborted when there is a core card switch or a SM switch to redundant card also.

srm3t3Xmtclksource.name: srm3t3Xmtclksource
srm3t3Xmtclksource.description: Indicates that the current clock source has been changed.

srm3t3LineEnable.name: srm3t3LineEnable
srm3t3LineEnable.description: Indicates that one T3 line has been enabled.

srm3t3LineDisable.name: srm3t3LineDisable
srm3t3LineDisable.description: Indicates that one T3 line has been disabled.

srm3t3FELineLpbkEnable.name: srm3t3FELineLpbkEnable
srm3t3FELineLpbkEnable.description: Indicates which DS1 or DS3 has been set in the loopback testing.

srm3t3LineLpbkDisable.name: srm3t3LineLpbkDisable
srm3t3LineLpbkDisable.description: Indicates which DS1 or DS3 has been reset from the loopback testing.

srm3t3AddLink.name: srm3t3AddLink
srm3t3AddLink.description: Indicates which T1 line from a T3 is added to which slot and which line.

srm3t3DelLink.name: srm3t3DelLink
srm3t3DelLink.description: Indicates which T1 line from a T3 is deleted from which slot and which line.

srm3t3DelSlotLink.name: srm3t3DelSlotLink
srm3t3DelSlotLink.description: Indicates which line is deleted from a slot

srm3t3NELineLpbkEnable.name: srm3t3NELineLpbkEnable
srm3t3NELineLpbkEnable.description: Indicates which DS1 or DS3 at the near end has been set for the loopback testing.

srm3t3NELineLpbkDisable.name: srm3t3NELineLpbkDisable
srm3t3NELineLpbkDisable.description: Indicates which DS1 or DS3 at the near end has been removed from the loopback testing.

srmLossOfClockTrap.name: srmLossOfClockTrap
srmLossOfClockTrap.description: Indicates a SRM T3 line lost clock source.

dsx1LineInAlarmTrap.name: dsx1LineInAlarmTrap
dsx1LineInAlarmTrap.description: Indicates line alarm exists 0x01 rcvRAIstate 0x02 xmtRAIstate 0x04 rcvAISstate 0x08 xmtAISstate 0x10 rcvOOFstate 0x20 rcvLOSstate

dsx1LineLpbkEnableTrap.name: dsx1LineLpbkEnableTrap
dsx1LineLpbkEnableTrap.description: Indicates that line loopback has been enabled

dsx1LineLpbkDisableTrap.name: dsx1LineLpbkDisableTrap
dsx1LineLpbkDisableTrap.description: Indicates that line loopback has been disabled.

trapLineEnabled.name: trapLineEnabled
trapLineEnabled.description: indicates line enabled. Applicable to AUSM and all FRSM cards except HS1 HS2 HS2B.

trapConfigChange.name: trapConfigChange
trapConfigChange.description: Sent when the config has changed. The bit map tells if the change on line/port/channel and the object index shows the line#/port#/channel#, the status shows if it's an add or mod or del.

trapSMclearAllCfg.name: trapSMclearAllCfg
trapSMclearAllCfg.description: Sent when the config is cleared.

redActiveatedTrap.name: redActiveatedTrap
redActiveatedTrap.description: Sent when the redundant card goes active

redRevertedTrap.name: redRevertedTrap
redRevertedTrap.description: Sent when the redundant card is reverted back to standby (reset first)

redAddedTrap.name: redAddedTrap
redAddedTrap.description: Sent when the redundancy is added

redDeletedTrap.name: redDeletedTrap
redDeletedTrap.description: Sent when the redundansy is deleted

trapChanOamLpbkStatus.name: trapChanOamLpbkStatus
trapChanOamLpbkStatus.description: Sent when the chan Ras_Oam_Loopback_state changes from Failed to Ok or Ok to Failed. It will carry status for a chunk of 256 channels as bitmaps. If the status of only 1 channel belonging to the chunk of 256 changes, trap is sent only for that chunk of 256 channels and not for any other chunk. For eg., suppose if channel 500 fails ras loopback test, trap is sent for the second chunk of 256 channels spanning channel nos 257 to 512.

dsx1StatLineAlarmTrap.name: dsx1StatLineAlarmTrap
dsx1StatLineAlarmTrap.description: Indicates the current statistical alarm State

trapChanStatusSummary.name: trapChanStatusSummary
trapChanStatusSummary.description: Sent when there are multiple channel failures and the total number of traps in 1 min exceeds the card level set thresholds. This trap is common to all the NBSM cards. viz. FRSM-8T1E1, CESM-8T1E1, AUSM-8T1E1, FRSM-VHS, CESM-T3E3 This traps informs the network management tool that the channel traps will not be sent from now but only summary traps will be sent at every 1 minute till the condition that is causing so many traps in quick succession goes away. This trap is not applicable to MGX Release 1.x.

trapPortAdded.name: trapPortAdded
trapPortAdded.description: indicates port added, currently this trap is not used

trapChanAdded.name: trapChanAdded
trapChanAdded.description: Sent when the chan is added, currently this trap is not used

trapChanActive.name: trapChanActive
trapChanActive.description: Sent when the chan is active

trapChanFailed.name: trapChanFailed
trapChanFailed.description: Sent when the chan is failed

trapChanDelete.name: trapChanDelete
trapChanDelete.description: Sent when the chan is deleted

egressDataBuffersOverflowTrap.name: egressDataBuffersOverflowTrap
egressDataBuffersOverflowTrap.description: Sent when the Egress Data Buffers are not available.

egressDataBuffersNormalTrap.name: egressDataBuffersNormalTrap
egressDataBuffersNormalTrap.description: Sent when the Egress Data Buffers are available.

x21LineLpbkEnableTrap.name: x21LineLpbkEnableTrap
x21LineLpbkEnableTrap.description: Indicates that line loopback has been enabled

x21LineLpbkDisableTrap.name: x21LineLpbkDisableTrap
x21LineLpbkDisableTrap.description: Indicates that line loopback has been disabled.

x21LineLpbkDetectedTrap.name: x21LineLpbkDetectedTrap
x21LineLpbkDetectedTrap.description: Indicates that line loopback code/condition detected.

x21LineLpbkRemovedTrap.name: x21LineLpbkRemovedTrap
x21LineLpbkRemovedTrap.description: Indicates that line loopback code/condition does not exist any more.

trapImaDisabled.name: trapImaDisabled
trapImaDisabled.description: Indicates that IMA group is disabled

trapImaActive.name: trapImaActive
trapImaActive.description: Indicates that IMA group is Configured

trapImaBandwidthChanged.name: trapImaBandwidthChanged
trapImaBandwidthChanged.description: Indicates that the bandwidth of an IMA group changed due to addition/deletion of links to/from the IMA group. This trap is Obsolete for MGX8850.

trapImaFailedAcpTimeout.name: trapImaFailedAcpTimeout
trapImaFailedAcpTimeout.description: Indicates that the IMA group was brought down due to ACP cells not being received within the expected interval. This trap is Obsolete for MGX8850.

trapImaFailedMajorAlm.name: trapImaFailedMajorAlm
trapImaFailedMajorAlm.description: Indicates that the IMA group failed due to major alarm on the IMA group This trap is Obsolete for MGX8850.

trapImaFailedSigFailure.name: trapImaFailedSigFailure
trapImaFailedSigFailure.description: Indicates that the IMA group failed due to an IMA signalling failure (eg: ACP cells are being received but the expected ones are not being received or an unexpected change in IMA-ID/LID on a link occurred etc This trap is Obsolete for MGX8850.

trapImaFailedBadDiffDelay.name: trapImaFailedBadDiffDelay
trapImaFailedBadDiffDelay.description: Indicates that the IMA group failed due to differential delay exceeding the maximum permissible for this IMA group. The variable 'imaObsDiffDelay' gives the current observed differential delay for this IMA group This trap is Obsolete for MGX8850.

trapImaRcvAisLoam.name: trapImaRcvAisLoam
trapImaRcvAisLoam.description: Indicates that the IMA is receiving a local OAM cell AIS from the remote end This trap is Obsolete for MGX8850.

trapImaRcvRdiLoam.name: trapImaRcvRdiLoam
trapImaRcvRdiLoam.description: Indicates that the IMA is receiving a local OAM cell RDI from the remote end This trap is Obsolete for MGX8850.

trapImaFailedOtherReason.name: trapImaFailedOtherReason
trapImaFailedOtherReason.description: Indicates that the IMA group failed due to a non- IMA protocol related failure. The value of imaPortState will denote the reason for failure.

trapImatmClockChange.name: trapImatmClockChange
trapImatmClockChange.description: Indicates that the current clock source changed from primary to secondary

trapImatmBadClockSource.name: trapImatmBadClockSource
trapImatmBadClockSource.description: Indicates that no good clock source is available

trapImaLinkInLoopback.name: trapImaLinkInLoopback
trapImaLinkInLoopback.description: Indicates that IMA Line Alarm exists. Can be lineLcpErr lineNotInLDS lineInLoopback

trapImatmDsx3HecChange.name: trapImatmDsx3HecChange
trapImatmDsx3HecChange.description: Indicate that the HEC Error Correction Option for DSX3 has changed. Can be Enable or Disable.

trapImaGTSMchange.name: trapImaGTSMchange
trapImaGTSMchange.description: Indicate the failure status of the IMA group(GTSM goes UP/DOWN)

trapImaCellRateChange.name: trapImaCellRateChange
trapImaCellRateChange.description: Indicates that the bandwidth of an IMA group changed due to addition/deletion of links to/from the IMA group

trapImaLinkStateChange.name: trapImaLinkStateChange
trapImaLinkStateChange.description: Indicates that the link in an IMA group is in LIF LODS or No Failure.

trapAusmPlppActive.name: trapAusmPlppActive
trapAusmPlppActive.description: Indicates that no PLPP alarm exists

trapAusmPortActive.name: trapAusmPortActive
trapAusmPortActive.description: Indicates that Port is Active and out of Alarm

trapAusmPortSvcRangeChanged.name: trapAusmPortSvcRangeChanged
trapAusmPortSvcRangeChanged.description: Indicates that Port SVC resource range has changed (used for ATM T1/E1 UNI ports)

trapImaPortSvcRangeChanged.name: trapImaPortSvcRangeChanged
trapImaPortSvcRangeChanged.description: Indicates that Port SVC resource range has changed (used for IMA ports)

trapPortIpChangedGeneric.name: trapPortIpChangedGeneric
trapPortIpChangedGeneric.description: Indicates that Ip change has been detected from the CPE connected to the ausm PORT

trapAusmChanActive.name: trapAusmChanActive
trapAusmChanActive.description: Sent when a Channel becomes active

trapAusmChanFailed.name: trapAusmChanFailed
trapAusmChanFailed.description: Sent when a Channel fails (In alarm)

trapAusmChanDelete.name: trapAusmChanDelete
trapAusmChanDelete.description: Sent when a Channel is deleted

trapAusmConDown.name: trapAusmConDown
trapAusmConDown.description: Sent when a AUSM Channel is brought down. This trap is not applicable to MGX Release 1.x.

trapAusmConUp.name: trapAusmConUp
trapAusmConUp.description: Sent when a AUSM Channel is brought up from down. The previous RowStatus of this channel must be outOfService. This trap is not applicable to MGX Release 1.x.

trapAusmChanReroute.name: trapAusmChanReroute
trapAusmChanReroute.description: Sent when a AUSM Channel is rerouted. This trap is not applicable to MGX Release 1.x.

trapAusmChannelAlarm.name: trapAusmChannelAlarm
trapAusmChannelAlarm.description: Sent when an AUSM logical channel is in Alarm, i.e. the channel can pass traffic within the PNNI n/w but is in Alarm because of CPE connectivity, or the line being in alarm. This trap is not applicable to MGX Release 1.x.

trapAusmChannelFailed.name: trapAusmChannelFailed
trapAusmChannelFailed.description: Sent when an AUSM logical channel fails, i.e. the channel cannot pass traffic within the PNNI n/w. This trap is not applicable to MGX Release 1.x.

trapCesmChanActive.name: trapCesmChanActive
trapCesmChanActive.description: Sent when a CESM Channel becomes active

trapCesmChanDelete.name: trapCesmChanDelete
trapCesmChanDelete.description: Sent when a CESM Channel is deleted

trapCesmChanUnderflow.name: trapCesmChanUnderflow
trapCesmChanUnderflow.description: Sent when a CESM Channel egress underflows

trapCesmChanOverflow.name: trapCesmChanOverflow
trapCesmChanOverflow.description: Sent when a CESM Channel egress overflows

trapCesmChanCellLoss.name: trapCesmChanCellLoss
trapCesmChanCellLoss.description: Sent when a CESM Channel Egress cell loss occurs

trapCesmChanActiveNew.name: trapCesmChanActiveNew
trapCesmChanActiveNew.description: Sent when a CESM Channel becomes active

trapCesmChanDeleteNew.name: trapCesmChanDeleteNew
trapCesmChanDeleteNew.description: Sent when a CESM Channel is deleted

trapCesmChanUnderflowNew.name: trapCesmChanUnderflowNew
trapCesmChanUnderflowNew.description: Sent when a CESM Channel egress underflows

trapCesmChanOverflowNew.name: trapCesmChanOverflowNew
trapCesmChanOverflowNew.description: Sent when a CESM Channel egress overflows

trapCesmChanCellLossNew.name: trapCesmChanCellLossNew
trapCesmChanCellLossNew.description: Sent when a CESM Channel Egress cell loss occurs

trapCesmChanIdleSuppStartNew.name: trapCesmChanIdleSuppStartNew
trapCesmChanIdleSuppStartNew.description: Sent when Idle suppression starts on this connection

trapCesmChanIdleSuppStopNew.name: trapCesmChanIdleSuppStopNew
trapCesmChanIdleSuppStopNew.description: Sent when Idle suppression stops on this connection

trapCesmChanActiveGeneric.name: trapCesmChanActiveGeneric
trapCesmChanActiveGeneric.description: Sent when a CESM Channel becomes active

trapCesmChanDeleteGeneric.name: trapCesmChanDeleteGeneric
trapCesmChanDeleteGeneric.description: Sent when a CESM Channel is deleted

trapCesmChanUnderflowGeneric.name: trapCesmChanUnderflowGeneric
trapCesmChanUnderflowGeneric.description: Sent when a CESM Channel egress underflows

trapCesmChanOverflowGeneric.name: trapCesmChanOverflowGeneric
trapCesmChanOverflowGeneric.description: Sent when a CESM Channel egress overflows

trapCesmChanCellLossGeneric.name: trapCesmChanCellLossGeneric
trapCesmChanCellLossGeneric.description: Sent when a CESM Channel Egress cell loss occurs

trapCesmChanIdleSuppStartGeneric.name: trapCesmChanIdleSuppStartGeneric
trapCesmChanIdleSuppStartGeneric.description: Sent when Idle suppression starts on this connection

trapCesmChanIdleSuppStopGeneric.name: trapCesmChanIdleSuppStopGeneric
trapCesmChanIdleSuppStopGeneric.description: Sent when Idle suppression stops on this connection

trapCesmConDown.name: trapCesmConDown
trapCesmConDown.description: Sent when a CESM Channel is brought down. This object is not applicable to MGX Release 1.x.

trapCesmConUp.name: trapCesmConUp
trapCesmConUp.description: Sent when a CESM Channel is brought up from down. The previous RowStatus of this channel must be outOfService. This object is not applicable to MGX Release 1.x.

trapCesmChanReroute.name: trapCesmChanReroute
trapCesmChanReroute.description: Sent when a CESM Channel is rerouted. This object is not applicable to MGX Release 1.x.

trapCesmChannelAlarm.name: trapCesmChannelAlarm
trapCesmChannelAlarm.description: Sent when an CESM logical channel is in Alarm, i.e. the channel can pass traffic within the PNNI n/w but is in Alarm because of CPE connectivity, or the line being in alarm. This object is not applicable to MGX Release 1.x.

trapCesmChannelFailed.name: trapCesmChannelFailed
trapCesmChannelFailed.description: Sent when a CESM logical channel fails, i.e. the channel cannot pass traffic within the PNNI n/w. This object is not applicable to MGX Release 1.x.

trapGenFrPortActive.name: trapGenFrPortActive
trapGenFrPortActive.description: Trap that is generated to indicate that a FR logical port has become active. Currently, this trap is used only in all flavours of FRSM-VHS card (FRSM-2CT3/T3/E3/ HS2).

trapGenFrPortFailed.name: trapGenFrPortFailed
trapGenFrPortFailed.description: Trap that is generated to indicate that a FR logical port has failed. Currently, this trap is used only in all flavours of FRSM-VHS card (FRSM-2CT3/T3/E3/HS2).

trapGenFrPortDelete.name: trapGenFrPortDelete
trapGenFrPortDelete.description: Trap that is generated to indicate that a FR logical port has become deleted. Currently, this trap is used only in all flavours of FRSM-VHS card (FRSM-2CT3/T3/E3/ HS2).

trapGenFrPortLoopbackEnabled.name: trapGenFrPortLoopbackEnabled
trapGenFrPortLoopbackEnabled.description: Trap that is generated to indicate that loopback on a FR logical port has become active. Currently, this trap is used only in all flavours of FRSM-VHS card (FRSM-2CT3/T3/E3/HS2).

trapGenFrPortLoopbackDisabled.name: trapGenFrPortLoopbackDisabled
trapGenFrPortLoopbackDisabled.description: Trap that is generated to indicate that loopback on a FR logical port has become disabled. Currently, this trap is used only in all flavours of FRSM-VHS card (FRSM-2CT3/T3/E3/HS2).

trapGenFrPortOvrSubscribed.name: trapGenFrPortOvrSubscribed
trapGenFrPortOvrSubscribed.description: Trap that is generated to indicate that a FR logical port has become oversubscribed. Currently, this trap is used only in all flavours of FRSM-VHS card (FRSM-2CT3/T3/E3/HS2).

trapGenFrChanActive.name: trapGenFrChanActive
trapGenFrChanActive.description: Sent when an FR logical channel becomes active: this trap is currently used only in all flavours of FRSM-VHS card (FRSM-2CT3/T3/E3/HS2).

trapGenFrChanFailed.name: trapGenFrChanFailed
trapGenFrChanFailed.description: Sent when an FR logical channel fails: this trap is currently used only in all flavours of FRSM-VHS card (FRSM-2CT3/T3/E3/HS2).

trapGenFrChanDelete.name: trapGenFrChanDelete
trapGenFrChanDelete.description: Sent when an FR logical channel is deleted: this trap is currently used only in all flavours of FRSM-VHS card (FRSM-2CT3/T3/E3/HS2).

trapGenFrsmConDown.name: trapGenFrsmConDown
trapGenFrsmConDown.description: Sent when a FRSM Channel is brought down. This trap is not applicable to MGX Release 1.x.

trapGenFrsmConUp.name: trapGenFrsmConUp
trapGenFrsmConUp.description: Sent when a FRSM Channel is brought up from down. The previous RowStatus of this channel must be outOfService. This trap is not applicable to MGX Release 1.x.

trapGenFrsmChanReroute.name: trapGenFrsmChanReroute
trapGenFrsmChanReroute.description: Sent when a FRSM Channel is rerouted. This trap is not applicable to MGX Release 1.x.

trapGenFrChannelAlarm.name: trapGenFrChannelAlarm
trapGenFrChannelAlarm.description: Sent when an FR logical channel is in Alarm, i.e. the channel can pass traffic within the PNNI n/w but is in Alarm because of CPE connectivity, or the line being in alarm. This trap is used for all FRSM flavors. This trap is not applicable to MGX Release 1.x.

trapGenFrChannelFailed.name: trapGenFrChannelFailed
trapGenFrChannelFailed.description: Sent when an FR logical channel fails, i.e. the channel cannot pass traffic within the PNNI n/w. This trap is used for all FRSM flavors. This trap is not applicable to MGX Release 1.x.

trapVismIpAddressChanged.name: trapVismIpAddressChanged
trapVismIpAddressChanged.description: Sent when the VISM card's IP address is changed.

trapVismChanActive.name: trapVismChanActive
trapVismChanActive.description: Sent when a VISM Channel becomes active. genericLineNum is always set to 0 since it is not applicable to VISM.

trapVismChanDeleted.name: trapVismChanDeleted
trapVismChanDeleted.description: Sent when a VISM Channel is deleted genericLineNum is always set to 0 since it is not applicable to VISM.

trapProtectedChanActive.name: trapProtectedChanActive
trapProtectedChanActive.description: Sent when vismChanActivityState transitions to active.

trapProtectedChanStandby.name: trapProtectedChanStandby
trapProtectedChanStandby.description: Sent when vismChanActivityState transitions to standby.

trapProtectedChanFailed.name: trapProtectedChanFailed
trapProtectedChanFailed.description: Sent when vismChanActivityState transitions to failed.

trapProtectedChanLocked.name: trapProtectedChanLocked
trapProtectedChanLocked.description: Sent when vismChanLockingState transitions to lock.

trapProtectedChanUnlocked.name: trapProtectedChanUnlocked
trapProtectedChanUnlocked.description: Sent when vismChanLockingState transitions to unlock.

trapVismCasVariantAdded.name: trapVismCasVariantAdded
trapVismCasVariantAdded.description: Indicates that an entry has been added to vismCasVarintTable.

trapVismCasVariantDeleted.name: trapVismCasVariantDeleted
trapVismCasVariantDeleted.description: Indicates that an entry has been deleted from vismCasVarintTable.

trapVismCasVariantConfigured.name: trapVismCasVariantConfigured
trapVismCasVariantConfigured.description: Indicates that casVariantState is transitioned to configured.

trapVismCasVariantNotConfigured.name: trapVismCasVariantNotConfigured
trapVismCasVariantNotConfigured.description: Indicates that casVariantState is transitioned to notConfigured.

trapVismScalarChange.name: trapVismScalarChange
trapVismScalarChange.description: Sent when a scalar object/objects changes. The bit map indicates the group to which the changed object/objects belong. For a single SET operation, a single trap will be sent per group, regardless of how many objects got changed in in that group.

trapVismTableChange.name: trapVismTableChange
trapVismTableChange.description: Sent when a table config has changed. The bit map tells which table got changed. and vismTrapIntIndex1 shows the index of the table entry which got changed. If there are 2 index values, the 2nd index will be contained in vismTrapIntIndex2. If the table has a string index, the index value will be contained in vismTrapStrIndex1.

trapVismCodecTemplateChanged.name: trapVismCodecTemplateChanged
trapVismCodecTemplateChanged.description: Indicates that the VISM Codec template has been changed.

trapVismModeChanged.name: trapVismModeChanged
trapVismModeChanged.description: Indicates that the vismMode has been changed on the card.

trapVismAal2CidAdded.name: trapVismAal2CidAdded
trapVismAal2CidAdded.description: Indicates that an entry has been added to the table vismAal2CidCnfTable.

trapVismAal2CidDeleted.name: trapVismAal2CidDeleted
trapVismAal2CidDeleted.description: Indicates that an entry has been deleted from the table vismAal2CidCnfTable.

trapVismHdlcChanAdded.name: trapVismHdlcChanAdded
trapVismHdlcChanAdded.description: Indicates that an entry has been added to the table vismHdlcChanTable.

trapVismHdlcChanDeleted.name: trapVismHdlcChanDeleted
trapVismHdlcChanDeleted.description: Indicates that an entry has been deleted from the table vismHdlcChanTable.

trapVismChanAdded.name: trapVismChanAdded
trapVismChanAdded.description: Sent when a VISM Channel is added genericLineNum is always set to 0 since it is not applicable to VISM.

trapVismChanFailed.name: trapVismChanFailed
trapVismChanFailed.description: Sent when a VISM Channel fails genericLineNum is always set to 0 since it is not applicable to VISM.

trapVismConDown.name: trapVismConDown
trapVismConDown.description: Sent when a VISM Channel is brought down.

trapVismConUp.name: trapVismConUp
trapVismConUp.description: Sent when a VISM Channel is brought up from down. The previous RowStatus of this channel must be outOfService.

trapVismChanReroute.name: trapVismChanReroute
trapVismChanReroute.description: Sent when a VISM Channel is rerouted.

trapVismAal2Muxing.name: trapVismAal2Muxing
trapVismAal2Muxing.description: sent when aal2 muxing type is changed.

trapVismFeatureChanged.name: trapVismFeatureChanged
trapVismFeatureChanged.description: Indicates that the vismFeatureBitMap has been changed on the card.

bnmCurclksourceTrap.name: bnmCurclksourceTrap
bnmCurclksourceTrap.description: Indicates that the current clock source has changed

bnmTrunkCellFormatTrapnum.name: bnmTrunkCellFormatTrapnum
bnmTrunkCellFormatTrapnum.description: This trap is sent out when the trunk cell format is changed. When a BNM-155 card is present it can be changed between UNI and NNI when there are no connections on the shelf. This is fixed for a T3/E3 card to STI format.

rasDskChksumStatusTrap.name: rasDskChksumStatusTrap
rasDskChksumStatusTrap.description: Indicates the Status of the SM configuration and FirmWare files. The Trap shows the number of corrupted PRI and Firmware files in the ASC from where it is sent. This Trap is sent everytime the diagnostics is completed.

rasDskBadSectorsTrap.name: rasDskBadSectorsTrap
rasDskBadSectorsTrap.description: Indicates the number of Bad Sectors in the ASC Hard Disk. If the number of Bad Sectors exceeds the threshold value, the rasDskHealth is set to FAIL. The threshold value is 30% of the total number of Sectors. This Trap is sent everytime the diagnostics is completed.

diagStatusTrap.name: diagStatusTrap
diagStatusTrap.description: This trap is sent out to report the results of the Diagnostics performed on the shelf. The diagtype varbind indicates whether this is the results of Power On Self Test (POST) or Online Diagnostics. For POST, this trap is sent only when POST fails and the diagTestId varbind specifies the test number of the first test that failed. For Online Diagnostics, this trap is sent whenever a diagnostics test configured as part of online diagnostics fails or passes. The traps is sent when the results of a diagnostic test changes from passed to failed or changes from failed to passed. The diagResult varbind specifies passed/failed and the diagTestId varbind specifies the test that failed.

shelfPowerOverLoadTrap.name: shelfPowerOverLoadTrap
shelfPowerOverLoadTrap.description: Indicates that the functionModuleType when inserted raised the total power consumption of the shelf beyond threshold value. functionModuleType value other(1) indicates that a fan tray has been removed, which increases the power consumption value beyond the capacity of remaining fan tray. shelfIntegeratedAlarm is set to the value major(3). When the alarm condition is cleared, the same trap is sent with shelfIntegratedAlarm value set to clear (1)

pxmCurClkSourceTrap.name: pxmCurClkSourceTrap
pxmCurClkSourceTrap.description: Indicates that the current clock source has changed

atmLineCellFormatTrap.name: atmLineCellFormatTrap
atmLineCellFormatTrap.description: This trap is sent out when the line cell format is changed. PXM lines can be configured to either UNI or NNI cell formats. STI format is not supported in MGX PXM.

secLineModuleRemovedTrap.name: secLineModuleRemovedTrap
secLineModuleRemovedTrap.description: Indicates whether or not a particular secondary (bottom) line module has been removed. This is applicable to MGX only, in a case where the front card(functionModuleType) is a full height card with 2 half height back cards.

secLineModuleInsertedTrap.name: secLineModuleInsertedTrap
secLineModuleInsertedTrap.description: Indicates whether or not a particular secondary (bottom) line module has been inserted This is applicable to MGX only, in a case where the front card(functionModuleType) is a full height card with 2 half height back cards.

secLineModuleMismatchTrap.name: secLineModuleMismatchTrap
secLineModuleMismatchTrap.description: Indicates that the front card does not support the secondary (bottom)line module. This is applicable to MGX only, in a case where the front card(functionModuleType) is a full height card with 2 half height back cards.

pxmApsDeactivateTrap.name: pxmApsDeactivateTrap
pxmApsDeactivateTrap.description: This trap indicates APS feature is deactivated for the working and protection pair. Severity = Clear NOTE: it is used by SRME too and the moduleSlotNumber will identify the source from PXM or SRME

pxmApsActivateTrap.name: pxmApsActivateTrap
pxmApsActivateTrap.description: This trap indicates APS feature is Activated for the working and protection pair. Severity = Clear NOTE: it is used by SRME too and the moduleSlotNumber will identify the source from PXM or SRME

pxmApsCardFailureTrap.name: pxmApsCardFailureTrap
pxmApsCardFailureTrap.description: This trap indicates abnormal condition on a PSM card which is used for APS feature. Severity = Major NOTE: it is used by SRME too and the moduleSlotNumber will identify the source from PXM or SRME

pxmApsLineFailureTrap.name: pxmApsLineFailureTrap
pxmApsLineFailureTrap.description: This trap indicates abnormal condition occurs on the working SONET line in the APS pair. Severity = Major NOTE: it is used by SRME too and the moduleSlotNumber will identify the source from PXM or SRME

pxmApsLineSwitchTrap.name: pxmApsLineSwitchTrap
pxmApsLineSwitchTrap.description: This trap indicates the APS line has been switched. The apsLineSwReason describes the switch reason. Severity = Minor NOTE: it is used by SRME too and the moduleSlotNumber will identify the source from PXM or SRME

pxmApsLineSwitchFailureTrap.name: pxmApsLineSwitchFailureTrap
pxmApsLineSwitchFailureTrap.description: This trap indicates abnormal condition occurs during the APS switch event. The apsLineSwFailureCode describes the failure reason. Severity = Major NOTE: it is used by SRME too and the moduleSlotNumber will identify the source from PXM or SRME

pxmApsStandbyLineFailureTrap.name: pxmApsStandbyLineFailureTrap
pxmApsStandbyLineFailureTrap.description: This trap indicates abnormal condition occurs on the protection SONET line in the APS pair. The apsLineFailureCode describes the failure reason. Severity = Major NOTE: it is used by SRME too and the moduleSlotNumber will identify the source from PXM or SRME

pxmApsCardClearTrap.name: pxmApsCardClearTrap
pxmApsCardClearTrap.description: This trap indicates abnormal condition on one of the PXM cards in this APS pair is cleared. Severity = Clear NOTE: it is used by SRME too and the moduleSlotNumber will identify the source from PXM or SRME

pxmApsLineClearTrap.name: pxmApsLineClearTrap
pxmApsLineClearTrap.description: This trap indicates abnormal condition on the working SONET line is cleared. Severity = Clear NOTE: it is used by SRME too and the moduleSlotNumber will identify the source from PXM or SRME

pxmApsStandbyLineClearTrap.name: pxmApsStandbyLineClearTrap
pxmApsStandbyLineClearTrap.description: This trap indicates abnormal condition on the standby SONET line is clear. Severity = Clear NOTE: it is used by SRME too and the moduleSlotNumber will identify the source from PXM or SRME

pxmApsConfigChangeTrap.name: pxmApsConfigChangeTrap
pxmApsConfigChangeTrap.description: This trap indicates sonet APS configuration changed

pxmApsModeMismatchTrap.name: pxmApsModeMismatchTrap
pxmApsModeMismatchTrap.description: This trap indicates that sonet APS architecture mode on the two ends of the APS pair is different. This mismatch will no cause a mode switch from 1+1 on the near end. Far end, if capable, may change its mode. If far end is not capable, manual intervention will be required. NOTE: it is used by SRME too and the moduleSlotNumber will identify the source from PXM or SRME

pxmApsModeMismatchClearTrap.name: pxmApsModeMismatchClearTrap
pxmApsModeMismatchClearTrap.description: This trap indicates sonet APS architecture mode mismatch is cleared. NOTE: it is used by SRME too and the moduleSlotNumber will identify the source from PXM or SRME

sonetXmtClkSrcChangeTrap.name: sonetXmtClkSrcChangeTrap
sonetXmtClkSrcChangeTrap.description: Indicates the transmit clock source changed

sonetXmtClkSrcLossTrap.name: sonetXmtClkSrcLossTrap
sonetXmtClkSrcLossTrap.description: Indicates that the transmit clock source is lost and a new clock source is in effect.

srmeAddLink.name: srmeAddLink
srmeAddLink.description: Indicates which Vt from a SRME Line is added to which slot and which line.

srmeDelLink.name: srmeDelLink
srmeDelLink.description: Indicates which Vt from SRME Line is deleted from which slot and which line.

srmeDelSlotLink.name: srmeDelSlotLink
srmeDelSlotLink.description: Indicates which line is deleted from a slot

srmeCnfLink.name: srmeCnfLink
srmeCnfLink.description: Indicates which Vt in which framing type is changed.

functionModuleHoldTrap.name: functionModuleHoldTrap
functionModuleHoldTrap.description: Indicates that a function module is in Hold state

trapConfigChangeRev2.name: trapConfigChangeRev2
trapConfigChangeRev2.description: Sent when the config has changed. The bit map indicates the change in card, line, port, channel, egress-q or resource partition configuration. The configChangeObjectIndex object shows the the line, port, channel, egress-q or resource partition index. The configChangeParentObjectIndex object shows the parent (higher level) index of configChangeObjectIndex. The configChangeGrandParentObjectIndex object shows the parent (higher level) index of configChangeParentObjectIndex. The configChangeStatus shows the operation type which can be add, mod or del. The configChangeSMSpecificObject is a generic object and based on the requirement can be used differently in each card type. The usage of the same is listed below. This trap is not applicable to MGX-8850 Release 1.x.x and MGX-8220

trapBbIfAdded.name: trapBbIfAdded
trapBbIfAdded.description: Indicates that Broadband Interface is Added .

trapBbIfActive.name: trapBbIfActive
trapBbIfActive.description: Indicates that Broadband Interface is Active.

trapBbIfDelete.name: trapBbIfDelete
trapBbIfDelete.description: Indicates that Broadband Interface is Deleted

trapBbIfFailed.name: trapBbIfFailed
trapBbIfFailed.description: Indicates that Broadband Interface is Failed ( In alarm )

trapBbIfCnfChange.name: trapBbIfCnfChange
trapBbIfCnfChange.description: Indicates that Broadband Interface configuration has been modified.

trapBbIfRscAlloc.name: trapBbIfRscAlloc
trapBbIfRscAlloc.description: Indicates that Broadband Interface Resource has been allocated to a network controller ( for e.g. PAR )

trapBbChanAdded.name: trapBbChanAdded
trapBbChanAdded.description: Indicates that Broadband Channel on user port of PXM is Added

trapBbChanActive.name: trapBbChanActive
trapBbChanActive.description: Indicates that Broadband Channel on user port of PXM is Active and No alarms exist.

trapBbChanDelete.name: trapBbChanDelete
trapBbChanDelete.description: Sent when a Channel is deleted

trapBbChanFailed.name: trapBbChanFailed
trapBbChanFailed.description: Sent when a Channel fails (In alarm)

trapRpmPortAdd.name: trapRpmPortAdd
trapRpmPortAdd.description: Indicates that a sub interface is added.

trapRpmPortDelete.name: trapRpmPortDelete
trapRpmPortDelete.description: Indicates that a sub interface is deleted.

trapRpmPortModify.name: trapRpmPortModify
trapRpmPortModify.description: Indicates that a sub interface is modified.

trapRpmPortActive.name: trapRpmPortActive
trapRpmPortActive.description: Indicates that a sub interface is Active.

trapRpmChanAdd.name: trapRpmChanAdd
trapRpmChanAdd.description: Indicates that a rpm channel is added.

trapRpmChanDelete.name: trapRpmChanDelete
trapRpmChanDelete.description: Indicates that a rpm channel is deleted.

trapRpmChanModify.name: trapRpmChanModify
trapRpmChanModify.description: Indicates that a rpm channel is modified.

trapRpmChanActive.name: trapRpmChanActive
trapRpmChanActive.description: Indicates that a rpm channel is Active.

parNodeStatusChange.name: parNodeStatusChange
parNodeStatusChange.description: This trap is generated when a alarm status of the node (parnNodeId) changes.

parNodeParmsChange.name: parNodeParmsChange
parNodeParmsChange.description: This trap is generated when a node (parnNodeId) parameters change.

parTrunkAdd.name: parTrunkAdd
parTrunkAdd.description: This trap is generated when a new trunk is added in the network.

parTrunkStatusChange.name: parTrunkStatusChange
parTrunkStatusChange.description: This trap is generated when the status of the trunk changes or the type of alarm changes.

parTrunkDelete.name: parTrunkDelete
parTrunkDelete.description: This trap is generated when the trunk is deleted from the network.

parTrunkConfig.name: parTrunkConfig
parTrunkConfig.description: This trap is generated when the trunk parameters are configured.

parUpConnStateChange.name: parUpConnStateChange
parUpConnStateChange.description: This trap is generated when a connection is upped. This trap is generated only by the node that masters the connection.

parDownConnStateChange.name: parDownConnStateChange
parDownConnStateChange.description: This trap is generated when a connection is downed. This trap is generated only by the node that masters the connection.

parConnAutoRemove.name: parConnAutoRemove
parConnAutoRemove.description: This trap is generated when a connection is auto removed.
